1. \(\Phi\) _is locally Lipschitz and the associated flow map_ \(\varphi\) _has infinite explosion time;_
2. \(\lambda\) _is such that_ \(u\mapsto\lambda(\varphi_{t,t+u}(x))\) _is integrable on_ \([0,\varepsilon(x,t))\) _for some_ \(\varepsilon(x,t)>0\) _and all_ \((t,x)\in\mathbb{R}_{+}\times\mathds{E}\)_._
